sentences: Born in Los Angeles, California, in 1952, Campbell was raised in New York City.
Throughout the 1960s, still unacquainted with the avant-garde movement, Campbell performed in the big bands of the Manhattan Community College.
From the 1970s onwards,  he performed primarily within the context of free jazz, spending some of this period studying with Yusef Lateef.
He died in January 2014 of hypertensive atherosclerotic cardiovascular disease at the age of 61.
